n
p
q
X(X_1,\ldots, X_n)
X_i=1
X_i=0
E(X_i)=p
E(X)=np
V(X_i)=pq
V(X)
V(X)=E(X^2)-E(X)^2
E(X^2)=np
E(X)^2=(np)^2
V(X)=np-(np)^2=np(1-np)
V(X)=V(X_1)+\cdots+V(X_n)
V(X)
V(X)=npq
X= \sum X_i
X^2 = \left(\sum X_i  \right)^2,
\sum \left(X_i^2  \right)
E[X^2] = E\left[\left(\sum X_i  \right)^2\right] = E\left[\displaystyle\sum_i \left(X_i^2  \right)\right] +  E\left[\displaystyle\sum_{i,j:i\not = j} \left(X_i X_j  \right)\right] = np + n(n-1)p^2
V[X] = E[X^2] - (E[X])^2 = np + n(n-1)p^2 - n^2p^2 = np-np^2
np(1-p)=npq
E(X^2)=np
n=2
p=1/2
 X^2=\begin{cases} 0 & \text{with probability }1/4, \\ 1 & \text{with probability }1/2, \\ 4 & \text{with probability }1/4. \end{cases} 
 E(X^2) = \frac32 \ne 1 = np. 
